  "purpose": "Labeled query corpus for the search-consolidation ablation harness (P2.2). Each query targets symbols/files that exist on this repo's main branch as of the corpus creation date. expected_paths lists files where a correct top-K hit must appear; the matcher should succeed if ANY hit's file_path matches ANY expected path (substring or exact, defined by the harness).",
  "categories": {
    "exact-symbol": "Identifier-shaped lookup (CamelCase, snake_case). Pipeline target: definitions search, name promotion path.",
    "symbol-intent": "Multi-word query that should resolve to one named symbol (mixed prose + identifier). Tests the reranker's intent classification + symbol-intent boost.",
    "test-intent": "Query implies the user wants test code. Tests `has_test_intent` and the test-intent override on NL path prior.",
    "file-path": "User wants a file by name/path fragment. Tests file-target search and basename matching.",
    "concept": "Natural-language behavior question, no specific symbol named. Tests NL path prior (production code over docs/tests/fixtures) and hybrid retrieval.",
    "qualified-name": "Partial qualified name (e.g. last segment of a dotted/colon-joined name). Tests the DB-rescue path that surfaces qualified-name definitions Tantivy buried."
  },
